data.description: If you are looking to embrace the tranquil beauty of Northern Michigan, than look no further than this charming log home nestled on a sprawling 9+ acre property in picturesque Benzie County. This home seamlessly combines, rustic charm with modern comfort. As you step inside, the high cathedral ceiling captures your attention, showcasing fine workmanship and quality materials that define this home. The full-log construction creates a warm and inviting atmosphere, making you feel right at home from the moment you enter. Start your day by sipping coffee on the covered front porch, and for a more private outdoor experience, enjoy a beverage in on the back patio which offers a serene view of the wooded backyard — a perfect spot to unwind and reconnect with nature. During those warm summer and fall days, you’ll be the envy of your friends and family, with a solar, heated pool that promises endless enjoyment. The spacious deck surrounding the pool is an ideal setting for entertaining, making it easy to host gatherings, and create lasting memories. An oversized 24 x 32 foot log-sided garage boasts 220 amp service and is finished with one by six cedar complete with a reclaimed tin ceiling sporting a patina finish. This property also features a 12 x 14 storage barn and an 8 x 8 garden shed, with a lean-to, ensuring you have ample space for all of your outdoor toys, equipment, and more. Recent updates include new paint in primary bedroom, all bathrooms, and new carpeting and paint in lower level. Conveniently located near the towns of Beulah, Benzonia, Honor, Frankfort, and 23 miles to Traverse City. Just 12 miles from the year-round excitement of CrystalMountain. This property offers the best of both worlds, secluded serenity and easy access to amenities and entertainment. Don’t miss your chance to experience the magic of northern Michigan living, where you can come home to comfort, style, and the serene beauty that this log home and property offers!
